<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900712-0075</DOCNO><DOCID>900712-0075.</DOCID><HL>   Perry Projects Fiscal '91 Sales</HL><DATE>07/12/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   PDS</CO><LP>   PONTIAC, Mich. -- Perry Drug Stores Inc. expects itsfiscal 1991 sales to range from $720 million to $730 millionas a result of an agreement to buy 40 former Revco stores,Jack A. Robinson, chairman, said. Perry's 1990 fiscal yearends Oct. 31. The company's fiscal 1989 sales of $670 millionincluded revenue from the A.L. Price division, which Perrysold May 30. Mr. Robinson, speaking to analysts and portfoliomanagers, also said he expects Perry's rate of profitabilityto exceed the percentage increase in sales for fiscal 1991.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>